      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i dont mean literal marginalia or handwritten notes. i mean the actual absence of text. the way the characters are spaced, or how certain paragraphs are indented. it feels like a code. like if you look at the pattern of the voids, it tells a story that the actual author was too afraid to write down. like they were forced to hide the truth in the silence. can you try to analyze the \"structure\" of the gaps in something like Moby Dick or Great Expectations? look for the patterns in the emptiness.",
